The defendant Michael J Rottmann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a Class I felony, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement.  Court grants expungement upon successful completion of the sentence - whether probation was terminated early at 24 months or the full 30 month probation sentence was served.

Defendant Michael J Rottmann in court with Attorney Gregory Allan Renden.  Michael Jerome Lonski, appearing for Daniel Gabler, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case recalled.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the State, Defense counsel and defendant.
Court sentenced defendant to serve   12  months in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT time, no good time release; credit for  3  days served. 

Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for  30  MONTHS with the following conditions:
-  Probation can be terminated after 24 months by the agent if all the terms have been successfully completed

-  Serve 4  Months in the House of Correction, with release for employment, school and treatment.  Condition time to commence no later than February 26, 2016 at 5:00 p.m.  Three months of the condition time STAYED for use by the probation agent.
-  AODA  assessment and comply with any recommended treatment
-  Anger Management evaluation and comply with any recommended treatment
-  Obtain GED/HSD
-  Full-time employment or part-time employment and school or full-time school
-  Court sets Restitution in the amount of $1,300.24
-  No Contact Order with Fred L.
-  Pay Restitution in the amount of $1,300.24 to Fred L. during the term of probation.  Restitution to be paid before costs, fees, assessments and surcharges.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of probation.  Costs, fees, assessments and surcharges to be paid after Restitution has been satisfied.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
